RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered I n Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALL forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the moderate pace while two wide through the turn, was roused at the top of the lane, collared JUSTHAPPENLIKETHAT in upper stretch, kept to task inside of the furlong marker and drove clear under steady late urging to prevail. BOUNDFORJAMAICA chased the moderate early pace, ran in pursuit while three wide on the turn, gained ground nearing the furlong pole, could not keep pace with ALL in deep stretch and ran on in the final stages to secure second. JUSTHAPPENLIKETHAT hopped slightly leaving the start, was hustled to get to the early lead and dictated terms to the turn, set moderate fractions to the quarter maker, was collared in upper stretch by ALL, chased that foe to the furlong grounds, weakened in deep stretch and was outfinished for second, while holding safely for third. HALF HOPING chased the moderate early pace, angled to the outside of rivals into the turn, raced three wide to the quarter marker, was coaxed four wide into the stretch and lacked a late rally. COASTAL STARLITE lacked early speed, saved ground through the turn, advanced in upper stretch, could not sustain that rally into the final furlong and did not threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONTINENTAL DIVIDE stalked the early pace while outside of rivals, raced three wide into the backstretch run, was well placed heading to the half-mile marker, made a steady gain while three wide into the stretch, came within aim of the leaders nearing the sixteenth-marker, rallied between runners in deep stretch and surged in the final strides to prevail. LOVE CANDY was allowed to settle, raced three wide into the backstretch run, advanced four wide on the second turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch, closed fast inside of the furlong pole while outside of rivals, came within aim inside of the sixteenth-marker, just missed for the win in the final strides and was up in time to secure the place. IL CAPITANO was asked to show speed leaving the break and set the early pace, set solid fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure at the quarter marker, battled with LOOKIN FOR REVENGE to mid-stretch, was able to hold that rival at bay into deep stretch, was confronted inside of the sixteenth-marker by oncoming top pair and was gamely bested in the final strides for the win and place, while holding for the show. LOOKIN FOR REVENGE forwardly placed early on, stalked the solid pace three wide into the backstretch run, advanced two wide approaching the quarter marker, battled for the lead in upper stretch, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was outfinished. NO HANG CHARLIE prominent in the early running, prompted the decent fractions through the backstretch run, stopped along the second turn, was eased through the stretch and walked off under his own power.

ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,set decent pace,met bid 1/8,gamely bested late,held 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHRIS FIX forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the modest fractions through the backstretch run, was roused two wide approaching the quarter marker, battled for the lead with PORT O' CALL to mid-stretch, drifted through the lane while kept to firm urging, was able to shake free from the stubborn runner-up in deep stretch and kept to task in the final stages to prove best. PORT O' CALL settled early on while never far back, raced two wide into the backstretch run, made a steady gain into the far turn, was roused three wide nearing the quarter marker, battled for the lead in upper stretch with CHRIS FIX, stayed right on that rival's flank into mid-stretch, could not match strides with CHRIS FIX inside of the sixteenth-marker and was outfinished, while besting the rest. TAKE THE TWO TEN allowed to settle in the early running, improved position nearing the half-mile marker, continued his advanced two wide along the second turn, gained ground nearing mid-stretch and came within aim at the furlong marker, was outkicked by the top pair in the late stages and held clearly at the finish for third. TIZ A THRILL assumed command leaving the break and showed the way into the first turn, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure nearing the quarter marker, was overtaken in upper stretch, chased the leaders to the furlong pole and faded in the final stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 6F All Weather Track CR: 91. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ZIPPY BABY allowed to settle early on while never far back, saved ground into the turn while advancing, was roused at the top of the stretch and tipped two wide for the drive, loomed at the furlong marker and overtook WICKLOW HILLS, took command and kept to task to the sixteenth-marker, inched away from the runner-up in deep stretch and held in a drive to prevail. SONOFAFINCH unhurried in the early running, advanced three wide on the turn, was roused four wide into the stretch, made a steady gain and came within aim at the furlong marker, was outfinished by ZIPPY BABY in the final sixteenth and bested the rest. WICKLOW HILLS engaged with MOB BOSS in the early stages and disputed the pace with that rival, shook free into the turn and set solid fractions through the quarter marker, led into upper stretch while on the left lead, was collared by ZIPPY BABY at mid-stretch, weakened in the late stages and held safely in the end for third. EL BERRINCHES chased the solid early pace, raced two wide along the turn, was steered three wide for the drive, Monroy lost his crop heading to mid-stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker and lacked a late rally. BALLROOM HUSTLER lacked early speed, saved ground through the turn and did not factor. MOB BOSS was a bit washy before loading and was fractious in the starting gate, was away in good order, contested the early pace with WICKLOW HILLS then took back off of that rival and stalked into the turn, advanced two wide nearing the quarter marker, was coaxed three wide into the stretch, lost position at the furlong marker and tired in the late stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M All Weather Track CR: 74. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOS VICIOS tracked the moderate pace, was roused two wide along the second turn, drew to even terms with EFFECTIVE GIG in upper stretch, battled with that rival to the furlong grounds, repelled EFFECTIVE GIG heading to the sixteenth-marker and drew clear under steady urging to the wire. EFFECTIVE GIG settled off of the early pace, maintained a three wide path into the backstretch run, inched closer heading to the half-mile marker, loomed three wide at the quarter pole, met the bid of DOS VICIOS in upper stretch, battled with that rival to the furlong pole, could not keep pace in deep stretch and was turned away, while just holding for second at the finish. SNAKE ISLAND was sent in the early stages and assumed command into the first turn, set modest fractions through the backstretch run, was overtaken nearing the quarter marker, stayed on well in the drive while chasing the leaders and was just outfinished for the minor awards in deep stretch. BIG DIFFERENCE was allowed to settle early on while never far back, saved ground to the second turn, raced two wide into the stretch and did not rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOTH AT FAULT well placed in the early running, rated just off of the pace while two wide through the turn, slipped to the rail in upper stretch, overtook CASH'S CAT nearing the furlong pole, met the bid of CHAOKOON inside of the furlong marker, dueled to the inside of that foe to deep stretch, drifted out in the final stages under firm left-handed urging and dug in at the finish to prevail. CHAOKOON unhurried in the early running, was roused four wide along the turn, loomed nearing the furlong pole, confronted BOTH AT FAULT inside of the furlong marker, dueled to the wire with that foe, could not get by the game winner in deep stretch and was denied for the win, while well clear of the rest. UPDRAFT chased the decent early pace, advanced while three deep on the turn, swung five wide into the stretch, was outrun to the furlong marker, lacked the needed late response but passed tiring foes in the final sixteenth and was up in time to secure third. CASH'S CAT prominent in the early running, pressed the decent early fractions, kept close attendance to SMOKIN BLAZE then took command nearing the quarter marker, led into upper stretch, was overtaken by BOTH AT FAULT at mid-stretch, faltered in the final stages and was just edged for third in the final strides. WOLF'S LIFE raced close to the decent early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, was outrun in upper stretch and gave way in the final furlong. WEE BEASTIE chased the decent early pace, raced two wide into the turn, slipped to the rail in upper stretch, lost position at the furlong grounds and weakened in deep stretch. SMOKIN BLAZE contested the early lead with several rivals then showed good early speed and set a pressured pace into the turn, battled with CASH'S CAT along the turn then lost the lead to that foe, dropped back leaving the turn and tired in the stretch drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Wee Beastie
ENTRY.OWNER: Fishbough William L and Fishbough-Miller Alyxandria

ENTRY.NAME: Smokin Blaze
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed,set pressured pace,dropped back stretch

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEALERS HAND allowed to settle, saved ground through the turn, was roused two wide in upper stretch, dove back to the inside and closed well at the furlong marker, responded to urging and rallied along the rail heading to the sixteenth-pole, surged in the final stages, caught STANFORD BAY in deep stretch and just held at the line to prevail in a blanket finish. GRIT AND CURIOSITY unhurried in the early running, kept a two wide path to the quarter marker, was roused at the top of the lane and came three wide into the stretch, closed well at the furlong marker, rallied inside of the furlong pole, split rivals while advancing inside of the sixteenth-marker, matched strides with DEALERS HAND to the finish and just missed for the win, while just getting up on the wire for the place. STANFORD BAY broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, set pressured fractions through the turn while off of the rail, shook free in upper stretch, kept to steady urging to deep stretch, was all out inside of the sixteenth-marker and was tagged on the line for the win and place, while just holding for the show. LIGHTINTHEDARKNESS lunged at the start and was off a step slowly, showed good early speed and pressed the solid pace into the turn, kept attendance to STANFORD BAY to the quarter marker, ran in pursuit of that rival to mid-stretch, closed in deep stretch and was outfinished in the final strides in a blanket finish. FULLY LOADED stalked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, raced four wide along the turn, swung five wide for the drive, made a mild gain at mid-stretch, closed in the final sixteenth but could not muster the needed late response.
